<div class="prose">

<p>A multi-criteria habitability simulator built specifically for the <a href="/units/unit-1/assessment-goldilocks-report/">Goldilocks Report</a>. Three modes: <strong>Explore</strong> (perturb any planet by hand), <strong>Load preset</strong> (12 presets — Earth, Mars, Venus + the 8 student-choice exoplanets + Kepler-22 b worked-example), and <strong>Compare</strong> (Earth, Mars, and your chosen exoplanet side-by-side with framework verdicts). Export the Compare view as JSON — the export includes a pre-formatted "For your AI Documentation Template" section you can paste directly into your Report.</p>

<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">This is a model</div>
  The calculator uses simplified physics: greenhouse adjustment is a 5-band lookup (not radiative transfer), magnetic field uses mass + age only (not rotation), atmospheric retention is a Jeans-escape lookup. Click <strong>Show assumptions</strong> inside the calculator to see every formula, lookup table, and known limitation. Apply OPVL to the calculator as you would to any source.
</div>

